00:37:38.220 --> 00:37:40.020
This is from "The red song"
put up by action books

00:37:40.020 --> 00:37:42.250
under Johana Sorenson's
visionary direction

00:37:42.250 --> 00:37:44.230
of the press.

00:37:44.230 --> 00:37:50.530
Preamble. "I am lighter, before
strangers I sing [inaudible].

00:37:50.530 --> 00:37:58.320
The prosperity of my tongue,
white animals, black animals,

00:37:58.320 --> 00:38:03.660
poison liquids, clear water,
the resurrection of the flesh,

00:38:03.660 --> 00:38:09.940
resurrection in all its forms,
sin, extreme unction, my scars.

00:38:09.940 --> 00:38:15.520
The Sinai song that hospital,
love, white sheets, barbed wire,

00:38:15.520 --> 00:38:18.220
poems that look like this.

00:38:18.220 --> 00:38:21.830
Illicit love, the
size of my hope.

00:38:21.830 --> 00:38:25.410
Licit love, the vacancy of some.

00:38:25.410 --> 00:38:31.130
Twilight of my life, my face in
the mirror after, clean scent.

00:38:31.130 --> 00:38:34.690
Urine scent of the
old and sick".

00:38:34.690 --> 00:38:38.980
"Cats, descent, dampness
in all its forms,

00:38:38.980 --> 00:38:42.000
imperfection, iron, truth.

00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:45.730
The delicate skin of
eyelids, canvas, closet,

00:38:45.730 --> 00:38:51.890
the word 'purity', yellow
benches, clarity, forgetting".

00:38:51.890 --> 00:38:56.800
"The black song", one.

00:38:56.800 --> 00:39:02.530
"I've seen you, brother combing
my hair like you'd pet a dog.

00:39:02.530 --> 00:39:06.790
Night flowers gesturing,
the body as stem.

00:39:06.790 --> 00:39:09.890
Hands extended to tongue.

00:39:09.890 --> 00:39:15.330
And the scanction of my
head, bread of beatitudes".

00:39:15.330 --> 00:39:19.160
Two, "I sleep now
with folded wings,

00:39:19.160 --> 00:39:21.590
lying in a wordless groove.

00:39:21.590 --> 00:39:26.210
I chew the dark fruit,
bittersweet like bread.

00:39:26.210 --> 00:39:34.230
Frozen honey, godless mask,
all the coupled black animals".

00:39:34.230 --> 00:39:41.780
Three, "perfection is this
ice, water startling the feet.

00:39:41.780 --> 00:39:50.160
Eyes licked by fever, taste of
the name dissolve in the mouth".

00:39:50.160 --> 00:39:56.070
Four, "at the end of
hands, darkness is as soft

00:39:56.070 --> 00:40:00.710
as your tongue, trailing
across my brain".

00:40:02.190 --> 00:40:06.620
Five, "vertigo curdles
in your eyes,

00:40:06.620 --> 00:40:10.550
an anguish of fish swallows
the stone of your tongue.

00:40:10.550 --> 00:40:16.050
Lucid birds at the
edge of clavicles".

00:40:16.050 --> 00:40:22.100
Six, "your ear bones cut
flowers hidden from rain.

00:40:22.100 --> 00:40:27.620
Your silence is perfect, like
a wineskin that won't drip.

00:40:27.620 --> 00:40:33.480
Nothing is left of me, just
the light shooting through".

00:40:33.480 --> 00:40:38.360
Seven, "the packs of
dogs maws cresses,

00:40:38.360 --> 00:40:41.840
shreds the anguish
of your breath.

00:40:41.840 --> 00:40:48.430
Octopus hair tangled in
fingers, legs pure as luces.

00:40:48.430 --> 00:40:52.890
There's no higher power
than these, my clavicles".

00:40:52.890 --> 00:40:57.630
Eight, "give me a glass of
water from your icy lap.

00:40:57.630 --> 00:40:59.710
Keep my teeth from freezing,

00:40:59.710 --> 00:41:04.170
shred this flower
sprouting under my tongue".

00:41:04.170 --> 00:41:09.020
Nine, "take my flesh
unbound, this weak pulse,

00:41:09.020 --> 00:41:11.120
protect me from wrinkles
of gawl.

00:41:11.120 --> 00:41:13.230
The acrid verb.

00:41:13.230 --> 00:41:17.910
I, who breaded my dead into
my hair, who sprayed myself

00:41:17.910 --> 00:41:22.500
with their scent, want to
go back to sowing my heart".

00:41:22.500 --> 00:41:24.550
So, that's some of Melissa.

00:41:24.550 --> 00:41:27.240
A beautiful poet, and I'm just
going to throw in a bonus poet,

00:41:27.240 --> 00:41:30.140
who's very young, born in 1983.

00:41:30.140 --> 00:41:32.570
Victoria Estol, and this is
book put out by "Toad" Press

00:41:32.570 --> 00:41:36.720
under Genevieve Kaplan's
direction, out in Los Angeles.

00:41:36.720 --> 00:41:38.540
And it's just one
poem by Victoria,

00:41:38.540 --> 00:41:40.570
from a book called
"Rolley Polley".

00:41:40.570 --> 00:41:44.110
It's titled in Spanish
"Bicho bola", from Yaguaru,

00:41:44.110 --> 00:41:46.600
the wonderful press
town in Montevideo.

00:41:46.600 --> 00:41:49.280
And this is Victoria Estol.

00:41:49.280 --> 00:41:53.100
"The bees use their stingers to
carve poems intro tree trunks,

00:41:53.100 --> 00:41:55.200
and the grasshoppers
are beautiful

00:41:55.200 --> 00:41:57.750
with their sad, attentive eyes.

00:41:57.750 --> 00:42:00.030
And all that we didn't
see during winter,

00:42:00.030 --> 00:42:03.460
because we believed it
frozen, begins to whisper,

00:42:03.460 --> 00:42:07.440
and suddenly we realize
we're surrounded by beauty.

00:42:07.440 --> 00:42:12.120
Pure, quiet beauty, which
is the most glorious kind,

00:42:12.120 --> 00:42:16.280
because its musicality
is almost inaudible.

00:42:16.280 --> 00:42:19.350
But if one listens hard
enough, it can be heard

00:42:19.350 --> 00:42:23.600
like a termite working
on a violin".

00:42:23.600 --> 00:42:24.900
Not one of those
[inaudible] hopefully.

00:42:24.900 --> 00:42:29.550
"It can be heard like a
termite working on a violin,

00:42:29.550 --> 00:42:32.210
that no one has touched
in years,

00:42:32.210 --> 00:42:36.540
but that the bug makes
sing while destroying it

00:42:36.540 --> 00:42:38.290
or not, who knows?"

00:42:38.290 --> 00:42:40.090
Thank you very much.

